          <msContents>
            <summary>
              <p>  </p>
              <p>468 fol.; Writing surface: parchment; Shelfmark: M. 74; Qurʾānic Text: complete Qurʾān codex; 14 lines per page; Dimensions: 213 x 213mm; Script style: kūfī.</p>
              <p> </p>
              <p>This entry is based on the catalogue of Fehmi E. Karatay (1888-1968). Currently we do not have access to the images. With exceptions, the catalogue does not contain precise information on the distribution of the text throughout the pages. For this reason, only fol. 1 is given. </p>
              <p> </p>
              <p><ref target="https://www.zotero.org/groups/corpuscoranicum_pub/items/itemKey/UEN2FUP7" sameAs="UEN2FUP7" type="zotero">Karatay (1962)</ref> describes the manuscripts as follows, p. 20: "58 M. 74 Kur’an. Parşömen. 213mm boy ve eninde cönk formasında 468 yaprak. Sahifede kûfi yazı 215mm uzunl.[uğunda] 14 [satır]. Tahminen III-IV. (IX-XII) asırda istinsah edilmiş olup ilk yaprağı sonradan parşömen üzerine sülüsle yazılmıştır. Miklepli kırmızı deri cilt. Tam bir Kur’andır."</p>
              <p> </p>
              <p>This can be translated as follows: "58 M. 74 Qurʾān. Parchment. 468 junk shaped leaves of 213 mm height and width. The text area [contains] 14 [lines] measuring 215 mm. Probably copied during the 3rd-4th (9th-12th) century and the first leaf are written later in Kufic script on parchment. Red leather binding with flap (miklep). The codex is a complete one/it is a complete Qurʾān codex."</p>
            </summary>
